- Ugh, Aya!

276
00:18:32,502 --> 00:18:34,296
- Come on already!
- Aya, seriously!

277
00:18:34,321 --> 00:18:35,589
We’re already here!

278
00:18:35,614 --> 00:18:36,762
Thank you!

279
00:18:38,889 --> 00:18:40,365
Aya, Alys!

280
00:18:40,853 --> 00:18:42,786
- Good morning!
- Good morning!

281
00:18:42,971 --> 00:18:44,389
Just wait here.
Drake is still sleeping.

282
00:18:44,414 --> 00:18:45,722
I’ll just wake him up.
He doesn’t want to get up.

283
00:18:45,747 --> 00:18:46,787
It’s Saturday today.

284
00:18:46,836 --> 00:18:49,100
Alys was also like that earlier.

285
00:18:50,170 --> 00:18:51,959
- Hey! Aya, seriously!
- It’s true!

286
00:18:52,521 --> 00:18:54,994
You’re really a
perfect match for my son.

287
00:18:56,074 --> 00:18:57,634
- Come in, feel at home!
- Is it not true?

288
00:18:57,819 --> 00:18:58,904
Okay, thank you!

289
00:19:01,325 --> 00:19:03,687
- Hello!
- Hello, Aunt Katrina.

290
00:19:03,767 --> 00:19:06,645
Sorry for disturbing
you on a Saturday.

291
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:08,437
This is for our school work.

292
00:19:08,963 --> 00:19:10,280
Of course!

293
00:19:14,528 --> 00:19:16,685
Does Aki know you’re here?

294
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:17,822
Who?

295
00:19:18,835 --> 00:19:21,022
Sorry, I mean Drake.

296
00:19:21,708 --> 00:19:24,294
I’m just used to
calling him Aki.

297
00:19:27,305 --> 00:19:28,305
Okay.

298
00:19:29,391 --> 00:19:30,826
Alys, Aya...

299
00:19:32,462 --> 00:19:33,558
Drake’s just taking a shower.

300
00:19:33,603 --> 00:19:35,192
He’s making himself handsome.

301
00:19:35,965 --> 00:19:38,229
You know, his girlfriend’s here.

302
00:19:39,845 --> 00:19:41,903
Yieee!

303
00:19:42,287 --> 00:19:43,758
Don’t be shy, Alys.

304
00:19:44,141 --> 00:19:46,064
Uncle Steve totally accepts you!

305
00:19:46,476 --> 00:19:48,162
Right, Uncle?

306
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:50,227
Of course! I consider her now
as my daughter-in-law!

307
00:19:50,725 --> 00:19:51,725
Right, Katrina?

308
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:58,384
She even introduced herself
as Alys Perez soon-to-be Palma!

309
00:20:02,032 --> 00:20:04,353
Is Aunt Katrina jealous of me?

310
00:20:04,912 --> 00:20:06,847
The stunning woman?

311
00:20:07,014 --> 00:20:09,968
Well, I can be fierce, too.

312
00:20:10,695 --> 00:20:11,695
Alys.

313
00:20:14,182 --> 00:20:15,189
- Hey!
- Ouch.

314
00:20:15,214 --> 00:20:17,401
Uncle Steve is
asking you something!

315
00:20:18,220 --> 00:20:20,283
Oh, sorry.
What was it again?

316
00:20:21,091 --> 00:20:24,259
He asked how you and
your Drakey baby met.

317
00:20:24,958 --> 00:20:25,958
Ah…

318
00:20:26,061 --> 00:20:29,305
Well, he transferred
to our school,

319
00:20:29,593 --> 00:20:30,996
and became my classmate.

320
00:20:31,021 --> 00:20:32,021
That’s it.

321
00:20:33,523 --> 00:20:34,523
How about you two?

322
00:20:34,858 --> 00:20:36,724
How did you and
Aunt Katrina meet?

323
00:20:37,269 --> 00:20:38,359
We met at school.

324
00:20:39,913 --> 00:20:41,264
You were classmates before?

325
00:20:41,775 --> 00:20:45,546
Oh, no. She used to
teach at Drake’s school.

326
00:20:45,632 --> 00:20:47,137
She just started teaching then.

327
00:20:47,162 --> 00:20:50,312
I was still trying to move on
when Drake’s mom died.

328
00:20:50,374 --> 00:20:51,500
It’s a long story.

329
00:20:51,531 --> 00:20:53,893
But Katrina helped
me to move on.

330
00:20:54,096 --> 00:20:57,046
Now, we’re getting
married in October.

331
00:20:57,272 --> 00:20:58,339
Oh my goodness!

332
00:20:59,853 --> 00:21:01,513
Oh, your boyfriend’s here!

333
00:21:02,554 --> 00:21:05,298
Aren’t you two
going to kiss, or hug?

334
00:21:06,682 --> 00:21:08,221
No “hi”, or “hello”?

335
00:21:08,638 --> 00:21:10,534
Aren’t you happy
to see each other?

336
00:21:13,282 --> 00:21:14,332
Hi.

337
00:21:15,340 --> 00:21:17,399
They’re still shy, Uncle.

338
00:21:17,751 --> 00:21:20,087
- Because there’s an audience!
- Aya!

339
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:23,699
Alright, I’ll get back to work.

340
00:21:23,761 --> 00:21:26,273
Hon, can you get the
papers I need to sign?

341
00:21:26,576 --> 00:21:28,179
Sure, hon, I’ll bring
them to your office.

342
00:21:28,204 --> 00:21:29,204
Alright.

343
00:21:30,988 --> 00:21:33,589
Come on, let’s go meet Drake.

344
00:21:34,607 --> 00:21:35,607
Thanks, hon!

345
00:21:37,004 --> 00:21:40,772
By the way, you can do your
business case report in Drake’s room.

346
00:21:40,882 --> 00:21:41,882
Dad!

347
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:49,394
Oh, wow. It’s unbelievable,
he can talk.

348
00:21:50,031 --> 00:21:51,749
Well, your room is clean, right?

349
00:21:53,839 --> 00:21:56,581
You are okay working
in Drake’s room, right?

350
00:21:56,606 --> 00:21:58,604
Of course, Uncle!
We’re okay with it. Right?

351
00:21:58,772 --> 00:21:59,815
- Uh...
- [scoffs]

352
00:22:00,549 --> 00:22:02,384
Go ahead and get started!

353
00:22:02,779 --> 00:22:03,779
Okay, Uncle!

354
00:22:03,965 --> 00:22:05,185
Go, go.

355
00:22:11,538 --> 00:22:12,538
Wait up!

356
00:22:12,748 --> 00:22:13,748
Hey!

357
00:22:14,005 --> 00:22:15,431
Hurry! Go after him!

358
00:22:15,691 --> 00:22:17,164
- Hurry!
- Ouch!

359
00:22:17,394 --> 00:22:19,072
Wait! I might fall!

360
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:23,783
Take it easy.

361
00:22:32,825 --> 00:22:34,811
This weirdo is so spoiled.

362
00:22:35,423 --> 00:22:39,088
His room’s practically complete—
he has everything.

363
00:22:39,283 --> 00:22:40,576
What more could you ask for?

364
00:22:41,313 --> 00:22:45,393
But why does it still
feel so flat and boring?

365
00:22:45,637 --> 00:22:49,079
I wouldn’t be surprised if
his personality feels the same.

366
00:22:49,629 --> 00:22:52,067
Because with all this stuff,

367
00:22:52,442 --> 00:22:54,704
his world looks
cold and lonely.

368
00:22:55,210 --> 00:22:56,418
Thank you, Drake!

369
00:22:58,840 --> 00:22:59,840
What is this?

370
00:23:01,170 --> 00:23:02,338
What’s inside this?

371
00:23:05,217 --> 00:23:06,655
Drake, can I borrow your laptop?

372
00:23:08,877 --> 00:23:10,649
Hey, did you ask for his permission?

373
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:13,467
I already did.

374
00:23:13,722 --> 00:23:15,702
Did he answer?
He didn’t, right?

375
00:23:17,270 --> 00:23:19,711
You know what you
need to learn?

376
00:23:19,856 --> 00:23:22,726
How to decipher Drake Palma 101.

377
00:23:23,068 --> 00:23:24,068
Lesson one:

378
00:23:24,164 --> 00:23:27,429
if you ask and he doesn’t
answer, that means yes!

379
00:23:28,090 --> 00:23:29,091
If he doesn’t want to,

380
00:23:29,116 --> 00:23:31,413
he would’ve taken the laptop
right away.

381
00:23:33,720 --> 00:23:38,734
Oh my, don’t tell me
you like Drake?

382
00:23:40,349 --> 00:23:41,349
Are you crazy?

383
00:23:42,861 --> 00:23:43,861
Dream on.

384
00:23:45,904 --> 00:23:46,904
What’s that?

385
00:23:54,808 --> 00:23:55,887
Is that for real?

386
00:23:56,152 --> 00:23:58,142
Shh! Keep it down!

387
00:24:13,410 --> 00:24:15,120
Your snacks are
ready downstairs.

388
00:24:15,201 --> 00:24:17,279
Aya, can you help me
bring them up here?

389
00:24:18,098 --> 00:24:19,433
Help him, hurry!

390
00:24:19,458 --> 00:24:21,247
Okay, Uncle.
I’ll be right there.

391
00:24:21,409 --> 00:24:22,944
- Come back right away.
- Yes!

392
00:25:01,082 --> 00:25:03,227
Where’s Aya?
I told her to hurry up.

393
00:25:12,928 --> 00:25:14,390
Aya!

394
00:25:14,838 --> 00:25:16,697
What are you up to now?

395
00:25:22,989 --> 00:25:25,257
Look at this one,
he’s just sleeping.

396
00:25:28,605 --> 00:25:30,148
Was he able to read all of these?

397
00:25:31,404 --> 00:25:33,378
Probably yes.
Because he’s smart.

398
00:25:35,116 --> 00:25:37,599
Hey, this looks good!

399
00:25:38,504 --> 00:25:41,458
Maybe we can use this for
our business case report.

400
00:25:48,101 --> 00:25:49,101
Ow!

401
00:25:51,077 --> 00:25:52,165
What’s that noise?

402
00:25:55,224 --> 00:25:57,617
Great. They finally went home.

403
00:25:58,410 --> 00:26:00,017
Ouch!

404
00:26:06,524 --> 00:26:09,990
Sorry for the mess.
I’ll clean it up.

405
00:26:13,068 --> 00:26:14,068
Come here.

406
00:26:16,116 --> 00:26:18,303
Hey! What are you doing?

407
00:26:25,750 --> 00:26:26,835
[scoffs]

408
00:26:35,552 --> 00:26:36,552
Here.

409
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:53,777
Don’t move, troublemaker.

410
00:26:55,578 --> 00:26:56,602
It will sting.

411
00:26:57,275 --> 00:26:58,296
Okay?

412
00:27:02,824 --> 00:27:03,911
He’s so close!

413
00:27:04,991 --> 00:27:06,501
What do I do?

414
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:09,491
Just close your eyes, Alys.

415
00:27:09,586 --> 00:27:10,842
Right, close your eyes.

416
00:27:12,130 --> 00:27:13,802
Then what?

417
00:27:14,440 --> 00:27:16,822
I can’t close my eyes
the whole day.

418
00:27:17,866 --> 00:27:21,512
Lord, what have I
gotten myself into?

419
00:27:36,429 --> 00:27:39,240
Oh no, is that my heartbeat?

420
00:27:40,314 --> 00:27:42,675
Hey, keep it down.

421
00:27:44,490 --> 00:27:46,157
Ouch! Let me do it!

422
00:27:58,045 --> 00:27:59,288
- It’s time to eat.
- Oh!

423
00:28:01,054 --> 00:28:02,054
Give me that!

424
00:28:12,148 --> 00:28:13,425
Whatever, Aya!

425
00:28:35,338 --> 00:28:37,745
Good thing you
finally met your match.

426
00:28:38,883 --> 00:28:40,877
I think you and Alys
look good together.

427
00:28:44,180 --> 00:28:45,180
But I want you.

428
00:28:47,461 --> 00:28:49,607
Aki, no.

429
00:28:51,521 --> 00:28:53,398
I’m about to marry your dad.

430
00:28:56,137 --> 00:28:57,638
Then why are you
still here with me?

431
00:28:58,903 --> 00:28:59,903
Like right now.

432
00:29:02,825 --> 00:29:05,067
We always talk in the wee hours.

433
00:29:07,460 --> 00:29:08,545
When everyone’s asleep.

434
00:29:10,582 --> 00:29:11,958
Doesn’t it mean anything to you?

435
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:15,873
Kat, be with me.

436
00:29:17,217 --> 00:29:18,406
Cut the engagement.

437
00:29:20,358 --> 00:29:22,994
Drake, you don’t understand.

438
00:29:36,044 --> 00:29:37,044
Sorry, Mom.

439
00:29:40,195 --> 00:29:41,529
I’m doing this all for you.

440
00:29:56,044 --> 00:29:57,778
Good morning, bestie!

441
00:29:57,921 --> 00:29:59,198
Did you have fun yesterday?

442
00:30:00,632 --> 00:30:03,968
Alys, one. Katrina, zero!

443
00:30:28,243 --> 00:30:29,243
Oh my god!

444
00:30:29,744 --> 00:30:31,830
What’s happening? Oh my god!

445
00:30:32,413 --> 00:30:34,373
No way!

446
00:30:34,916 --> 00:30:38,514
Erase, erase! No!

447
00:30:41,297 --> 00:30:42,501
Where are you, bestie?

448
00:30:42,549 --> 00:30:43,900
I really want to go home!

449
00:30:43,925 --> 00:30:45,019
Should I wait for you?

450
00:30:45,385 --> 00:30:47,234
I’ve been here for a while now.
What’s taking you so long?

451
00:30:47,513 --> 00:30:48,553
Come on, Aya.

452
00:30:55,182 --> 00:30:56,182
Ah!

453
00:31:14,956 --> 00:31:15,956
Troublemaker.

454
00:31:17,676 --> 00:31:18,676
You okay?

455
00:31:33,224 --> 00:31:34,267
Did your knees get hurt?

456
00:31:37,478 --> 00:31:38,478
Don’t move.

457
00:31:41,566 --> 00:31:42,566
Hop on.

458
00:31:44,416 --> 00:31:45,416
Huh?

459
00:31:45,649 --> 00:31:46,649
Hop on.

460
00:31:48,031 --> 00:31:49,973
Your house is nearby, right?

461
00:31:50,709 --> 00:31:52,109
Show me the way,
I’ll walk you home.

462
00:31:54,234 --> 00:31:55,443
Thank you.

463
00:32:18,227 --> 00:32:20,146
Dela Cruz, Lance Miguel.

464
00:32:25,401 --> 00:32:26,527
De Joya, Albert.

465
00:32:30,406 --> 00:32:32,437
Alys Zyril Perez.

466
00:32:48,475 --> 00:32:50,931
I knew it, we’re soulmates.

467
00:32:51,512 --> 00:32:52,679
Can you believe it, bestie?

468
00:32:53,317 --> 00:32:55,069
We both got F’s!

469
00:32:56,557 --> 00:32:57,947
You’re crazy.

470
00:32:57,976 --> 00:33:00,280
We both failed and
you’re happy about it.

471
00:33:02,063 --> 00:33:03,784
- Go, sit down!
- Fine!

472
00:33:03,955 --> 00:33:05,039
Okay, listen up!

473
00:33:05,300 --> 00:33:06,300
By the looks of it,

474
00:33:06,632 --> 00:33:09,987
some of you will need
to take tutorial sessions.

475
00:33:10,863 --> 00:33:12,493
And it will begin tomorrow.

476
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:15,574
You better tell your
parents about this.

477
00:33:16,257 --> 00:33:19,886
Those who received F’s
will take the said classes.

478
00:33:20,289 --> 00:33:23,872
while those who received
A’s will be the tutors.

479
00:33:25,122 --> 00:33:26,265
Is that clear?

480
00:33:26,337 --> 00:33:28,262
Yes, sir!

481
00:33:28,339 --> 00:33:31,011
I will be posting the
pairings later this afternoon.

482
00:33:39,126 --> 00:33:40,907
What’s all the commotion about?

483
00:33:44,627 --> 00:33:48,360
Let’s go, bestie. Let’s check the list.
I’m so excited.

484
00:33:49,180 --> 00:33:52,943
Since when do tutorial lessons
become exciting, bestie?

485
00:33:55,867 --> 00:33:57,080
Let’s go!

486
00:33:57,861 --> 00:34:00,375
Wait! Just wait!

487
00:34:01,289 --> 00:34:03,247
- Excuse me.
- Excuse me.

488
00:34:03,313 --> 00:34:04,581
- Excuse me.
- Excuse me.

489
00:34:04,628 --> 00:34:05,974
Excuse me.

490
00:34:06,273 --> 00:34:07,383
Excuse me.

491
00:34:09,915 --> 00:34:11,340
Would you look at that?

492
00:34:12,094 --> 00:34:14,370
Drake’s your tutor.

493
00:34:14,802 --> 00:34:17,096
You’re really meant to be!

494
00:34:17,582 --> 00:34:20,990
Nice! I don’t need to
be a matchmaker anymore!

495
00:34:30,109 --> 00:34:32,660
Why is Sheen my loves
your tutor?

496
00:34:33,858 --> 00:34:36,190
Oh, CB’s my tutor!

497
00:34:36,595 --> 00:34:37,595
What is CB?

498
00:34:39,428 --> 00:34:40,428
Cry baby.

499
00:34:40,707 --> 00:34:43,959
Because he’s
always crying over Kei.

500
00:34:44,439 --> 00:34:46,052
He’s acting like they’re married.

501
00:34:46,418 --> 00:34:47,542
Excuse me!

502
00:34:50,104 --> 00:34:53,950
Hey, you! Don’t mess
with Sheen my loves!

503
00:34:55,477 --> 00:34:57,688
I can’t promise that, bestie!

504
00:34:59,083 --> 00:35:00,865
You’re really something!

505
00:35:00,890 --> 00:35:03,607
What’s your problem?
Do you want me to whack you? Let’s go!

506
00:35:06,225 --> 00:35:08,812
I don’t want that Drake Palma
to call me dumb.

507
00:35:10,108 --> 00:35:11,633
I’m actually nice, okay?

508
00:35:23,788 --> 00:35:27,646
I’m still at the Demographics part
and I already feel like crying!

509
00:35:30,452 --> 00:35:32,931
Oh, that was a good dinner.

510
00:35:34,575 --> 00:35:40,738
Well, someone’s busy studying!

511
00:35:42,014 --> 00:35:43,468
I have to.

512
00:35:44,142 --> 00:35:47,171
I’m part of the
tutorial program.

513
00:35:48,020 --> 00:35:50,473
Wow, so proud of you, princess!

514
00:35:50,690 --> 00:35:52,139
So, who’s the lucky student?

515
00:35:54,235 --> 00:35:55,635
I’m the student.

516
00:35:59,615 --> 00:36:01,829
Sorry, Mom. Sorry, Dad.

517
00:36:03,642 --> 00:36:04,642
You know what?

518
00:36:04,760 --> 00:36:08,305
Just think of it this way—
through the tutorial lessons,

519
00:36:08,408 --> 00:36:12,473
at least you’re reviewing early
for college entrance exams, right?

520
00:36:12,935 --> 00:36:15,939
Well, Alys,
you know the dream, right?

521
00:36:16,217 --> 00:36:19,933
You need to get into
St. Collete Academy. Yes?

522
00:36:20,238 --> 00:36:21,238
Yes, Mom.

523
00:36:21,681 --> 00:36:26,084
Just focus. We know
you can do it, okay?

524
00:36:28,272 --> 00:36:29,815
Okay, Mom. Thanks.

525
00:36:30,829 --> 00:36:33,791
Alright. Just study well,
study hard.

526
00:36:33,875 --> 00:36:34,946
I’ll leave you be.

527
00:36:35,191 --> 00:36:36,588
I’ll go ahead, okay?

528
00:36:37,705 --> 00:36:39,839
- Thanks, mom. Good night.
- Good night!

529
00:36:39,864 --> 00:36:40,864
Love you!

530
00:36:43,993 --> 00:36:44,993
You got this, sweetheart.

531
00:36:46,329 --> 00:36:47,329
Good night.

532
00:36:47,455 --> 00:36:48,455
Thanks, Dad.

533
00:36:54,761 --> 00:36:55,761
You can do it.

534
00:36:55,786 --> 00:36:57,212
So, what did your mom say?

535
00:36:58,397 --> 00:36:59,621
Of course, she got mad.

536
00:37:00,259 --> 00:37:03,012
She asked why I’m always
part of the tutorial program.

537
00:37:03,313 --> 00:37:06,699
I told her, just think
of it as free tutorial.

538
00:37:06,724 --> 00:37:07,724
It saves money, right?

539
00:37:08,726 --> 00:37:09,807
Makes sense!

540
00:37:09,852 --> 00:37:11,479
- Yeah, true.
- I’m clever, huh?

541
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:12,800
- You’re totally insane.
- Right?

542
00:37:14,649 --> 00:37:16,009
Look who’s here!

543
00:37:16,109 --> 00:37:17,548
Boring!

544
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:18,987
You’re not the stars
of Mean Girls,

545
00:37:19,012 --> 00:37:20,327
so drop the attitude.

546
00:37:20,374 --> 00:37:23,297
Whatever, Miss Whoever You Are.

547
00:37:23,322 --> 00:37:24,504
My name is Aya.

548
00:37:24,611 --> 00:37:26,924
[laughing]

549
00:37:26,949 --> 00:37:27,952
Losers.

550
00:37:27,977 --> 00:37:29,180
- You’re cheap.
- Losers!

551
00:37:29,205 --> 00:37:30,665
- Let’s go, girls.
- Yeah, go.

552
00:37:30,690 --> 00:37:32,298
What a waste of time.

553
00:37:32,973 --> 00:37:33,975
Ahem!

554
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:35,000
By the way,

555
00:37:35,490 --> 00:37:39,173
don’t you dare seduce Drake
during your tutorials, okay?

556
00:37:40,594 --> 00:37:41,762
Excuse me.

557
00:37:42,710 --> 00:37:44,888
Why would I have to
seduce Drake Palma?

558
00:37:45,554 --> 00:37:47,198
He’s already my boyfriend.

559
00:37:47,266 --> 00:37:50,076
- Wow!
- Boyfriend?

560
00:37:50,101 --> 00:37:51,143
Boyfriend?

561
00:37:51,769 --> 00:37:53,621
You think I’d believe that?

562
00:37:53,646 --> 00:37:56,153
I’m not dumb, okay?

563
00:37:59,304 --> 00:38:00,306
Right!

564
00:38:00,331 --> 00:38:03,302
He’s my partner for
the acquaintance party!

565
00:38:03,542 --> 00:38:04,542
Partner?

566
00:38:06,033 --> 00:38:07,033
Partner?

567
00:38:07,058 --> 00:38:09,738
[girls laughing]

568
00:38:10,937 --> 00:38:12,895
Okay then, Miss Pathetic.

569
00:38:13,641 --> 00:38:14,781
Show us.

570
00:38:20,756 --> 00:38:21,918
Bye!

571
00:38:23,137 --> 00:38:24,708
I’m so proud of you, bestie!

572
00:38:25,095 --> 00:38:27,705
But how are you going to
tell your boyfriend about it?

573
00:38:40,735 --> 00:38:41,735
Let’s go, Alys!

574
00:38:41,944 --> 00:38:42,944
You can do this!

575
00:38:42,987 --> 00:38:43,987
You can do it!

576
00:38:47,491 --> 00:38:48,816
You can do it! Let’s go!

577
00:38:57,208 --> 00:38:58,390
Um...

578
00:38:59,337 --> 00:39:00,337
Drake…

579
00:39:04,342 --> 00:39:05,342
Um...

580
00:39:07,345 --> 00:39:08,635
You know...

581
00:39:12,516 --> 00:39:14,018
About the....

582
00:39:14,705 --> 00:39:16,713
Acquaintance party.

583
00:39:18,898 --> 00:39:19,898
Um...

584
00:39:20,649 --> 00:39:21,649
No.

585
00:39:23,444 --> 00:39:24,444
Huh?

586
00:39:36,015 --> 00:39:39,143
No? As in?

587
00:39:39,168 --> 00:39:42,267
No, as in I won’t
go to that party!

588
00:39:48,253 --> 00:39:49,253
Ah!

589
00:39:51,222 --> 00:39:52,222
Ouch.

590
00:39:53,182 --> 00:39:54,600
That hurts.

591
00:39:57,686 --> 00:39:58,686
That hurts.

592
00:40:01,275 --> 00:40:03,665
It hurts being rejected
by your crush.

593
00:40:06,112 --> 00:40:07,252
Crush?

594
00:40:07,780 --> 00:40:09,530
I have a crush on Drake Palma?

595
00:40:10,324 --> 00:40:12,724
Oh no!

596
00:40:13,294 --> 00:40:14,548
Shhh!

597
00:40:15,714 --> 00:40:17,080
This can’t be happening!

598
00:40:20,668 --> 00:40:21,783
But seriously…

599
00:40:22,586 --> 00:40:24,403
do I have a crush
on that weirdo?

600
00:40:41,355 --> 00:40:42,908
Thank you, Sir! Bye!

601
00:40:46,330 --> 00:40:48,907
What are you doing here?

602
00:40:50,599 --> 00:40:51,599
What else?

603
00:40:51,648 --> 00:40:53,279
I’m stressed at home.

604
00:40:54,162 --> 00:40:56,414
My mom keeps on asking
about the color of Kei’s dress,

605
00:40:56,882 --> 00:40:58,722
so she can buy me
a matching tie.

606
00:40:59,054 --> 00:41:00,134
That’s it?

607
00:41:00,624 --> 00:41:02,556
You should’ve just called me!

608
00:41:04,378 --> 00:41:05,926
We’re not even partners.

609
00:41:06,855 --> 00:41:07,855
She doesn’t want to.

610
00:41:09,982 --> 00:41:11,154
Sheen…

611
00:41:13,098 --> 00:41:14,466
What about you?
Do you have a partner?

612
00:41:14,620 --> 00:41:15,620
As if.

613
00:41:15,890 --> 00:41:17,043
I don’t have one.

614
00:41:22,302 --> 00:41:23,856
What if we go together?

615
00:41:28,948 --> 00:41:32,134
I mean… we’re best friends, right?

616
00:41:34,187 --> 00:41:35,187
You don’t want to?

617
00:41:37,238 --> 00:41:39,958
Crazy! Of course I do!

618
00:41:41,014 --> 00:41:42,102
Are you serious?

619
00:41:42,821 --> 00:41:44,135
We’re partners now?

620
00:41:46,462 --> 00:41:47,462
It’s a date.

621
00:41:47,755 --> 00:41:48,755
It’s a date!

622
00:41:49,841 --> 00:41:51,066
- You want to practice?
- Sure.

623
00:41:51,091 --> 00:41:52,884
- Let’s try it out.
- Alright, let’s go.

624
00:42:16,723 --> 00:42:18,831
I think I’ll go with
this pink one, Mom.

625
00:42:18,891 --> 00:42:21,706
Perfect! That’s actually the
one I was hoping you’d pick.

626
00:42:21,776 --> 00:42:23,834
I think it will
look best on you!

627
00:42:24,216 --> 00:42:25,952
So, final answer?

628
00:42:26,377 --> 00:42:28,854
- Yes, Mom, final answer.
- Great!

629
00:42:28,898 --> 00:42:31,049
Okay, I’ll let my team
work on this one.

630
00:42:31,515 --> 00:42:34,469
By the way, do you have
a partner for the party?

631
00:42:34,593 --> 00:42:36,431
I don’t need to know the name.

632
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:41,995
I just thought it would be cute
if he’ll match your outfit, right?

633
00:42:43,138 --> 00:42:45,741
Okay, I’ll work on this one tonight.

634
00:42:45,820 --> 00:42:47,949
You get some rest now.

635
00:42:48,065 --> 00:42:49,315
Good night, my dear!

636
00:42:49,645 --> 00:42:51,512
Good night, mom. Thank you.

637
00:43:09,719 --> 00:43:10,719
Hello?

638
00:43:12,139 --> 00:43:13,184
What did you pick?

639
00:43:13,424 --> 00:43:14,897
The one I showed you!

640
00:43:15,050 --> 00:43:17,105
Nice! Good choice!

641
00:43:18,263 --> 00:43:21,955
Wow, for the first time,
you’re supportive, bestie.

642
00:43:22,657 --> 00:43:25,172
But guess what?
I have better news for you.

643
00:43:25,625 --> 00:43:26,625
What?

644
00:43:27,363 --> 00:43:29,983
Guess who my partner is!

645
00:43:32,234 --> 00:43:33,527
You got Drake to go with you?

646
00:43:34,695 --> 00:43:36,133
Who cares about Drake!

647
00:43:36,291 --> 00:43:37,592
He can do whatever he wants.

648
00:43:38,969 --> 00:43:42,034
Sheen my loves is my partner!

649
00:43:42,100 --> 00:43:44,315
What? CB?

650
00:43:44,747 --> 00:43:45,747
Yup!

651
00:43:46,421 --> 00:43:49,594
As they say, good things
come to those who wait!

652
00:43:53,897 --> 00:43:54,898
Hello?

653
00:43:56,468 --> 00:43:57,468
Hello?

654
00:43:57,843 --> 00:43:58,843
Aya, you there?

655
00:44:01,805 --> 00:44:02,805
Ugh!

656
00:44:12,566 --> 00:44:21,095
Presenting, my not so baby
girl anymore– Alys Zyril Perez!

657
00:44:28,248 --> 00:44:29,781
You look amazing, princess.

658
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:34,115
Thank you, Dad!

659
00:44:34,254 --> 00:44:35,435
Thank you, Mom!

660
00:44:35,934 --> 00:44:38,651
I’m so excited!
You guys are the best!

661
00:44:38,676 --> 00:44:39,777
Are you ready, baby?

662
00:44:39,962 --> 00:44:42,433
Yes! I’m so excited!

663
00:45:07,579 --> 00:45:08,650
Are you okay, baby?

664
00:45:08,872 --> 00:45:10,430
Yes, mom. Of course!

665
00:45:11,250 --> 00:45:12,531
Have you heard from Sheen yet?

666
00:45:13,595 --> 00:45:15,537
I think he’s just
stuck in traffic, Dad.

667
00:45:15,887 --> 00:45:18,534
Can I wait outside?

668
00:45:18,807 --> 00:45:23,006
So I can see him
when he gets here.

669
00:45:24,592 --> 00:45:27,100
Yeah, it’s okay.
No problem.

670
00:45:27,266 --> 00:45:29,406
Let me know if you
need anything, princess.

671
00:45:29,596 --> 00:45:31,033
Thanks, Dad. Thanks, Mom.

672
00:47:00,529 --> 00:47:01,949
Am I dreaming?

673
00:47:03,925 --> 00:47:04,925
Hey.

674
00:47:10,786 --> 00:47:11,786
Let’s go.

675
00:47:42,234 --> 00:47:43,751
Ouch! Let me do it!

676
00:47:57,583 --> 00:47:58,802
Is that her heartbeat?

677
00:48:02,158 --> 00:48:03,329
- It’s time to eat!
- Oh!

678
00:48:05,132 --> 00:48:06,132
Give me that!

679
00:48:10,489 --> 00:48:11,510
Or mine?

680
00:48:14,808 --> 00:48:18,250
On the next episode of
Seducing Drake Palma

681
00:48:18,275 --> 00:48:20,927
My date’s so
handsome tonight, right?

682
00:48:21,273 --> 00:48:23,358
What can you say, Kei?

683
00:48:24,335 --> 00:48:25,401
You ditched me!

684
00:48:25,967 --> 00:48:28,105
Aya said you were
going with Drake.

685
00:48:28,322 --> 00:48:29,572
So I went with her instead!

686
00:48:38,094 --> 00:48:39,099
Drake!

687
00:48:39,124 --> 00:48:41,366
Maybe you just forced
him to go with you.

688
00:48:42,558 --> 00:48:45,078
Drake, everyone’s staring at us.

689
00:48:45,299 --> 00:48:46,384
Don’t mind them.

690
00:48:46,429 --> 00:48:47,429
But–

691
00:48:52,749 --> 00:48:56,477
I can hear the jealousy in your
voice because Drake is my partner.

692
00:48:56,502 --> 00:48:58,687
I'm the queen of the night.
